Write a program to accept number from user display addition, multiple,
subtraction, division.

import java.util.*;
public class Arithmetic {
 public static void main(String args[]) {
 int first, second, add, subtract, multiply;
 float divide;
 Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
 System.out.println("Irfan Ali, Roll No: 9");
 System.out.println("Enter Two Numbers: ");
 first = sc.nextInt();
 second = sc.nextInt();
 add = first + second;
 subtract = first - second;
 multiply = first * second;
 divide = (float) first / second;
 System.out.println("Sum = " + add);
 System.out.println("Difference = " + subtract);
 System.out.println("Multiplication = " + multiply);
 System.out.println("Division = " + divide);
 sc.close();
 }
}



Write a program to accept a number from user and check whether it is even or odd.

import java.util.*;
public class EvenOrOdd {
 public static void main(String[] args) {
 System.out.println("Irfan Ali, Rollno: 9");
 Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);


 System.out.print("Enter a number: ");
 int number = scanner.nextInt();


 if (number % 2 == 0) {
 System.out.println("The number is even.");
 } else {
 System.out.println("The number is odd.");
 }



 }
}




Write a program to accept two numbers from the user and display the larger number using conditional operator.

import java.util.*;
public class LargerNumber {
 public static void main(String[] args) {
 System.out.println("Irfan Ali, Rollno: 9");
 Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

 System.out.print("Enter the first number: ");
 int num1 = scanner.nextInt();

 System.out.print("Enter the second number: ");
 int num2 = scanner.nextInt();

 int larger = (num1 > num2) ? num1 : num2;

 System.out.println("The larger number is: " + larger);


 }
}




Write a program to accept name, roll no, percentage from the user usingcommand line argument and display the same.
import java.util.*;

public class StudentInfo {
 public static void main(String[] args) {
 System.out.println("Irfan Ali, Rollno: 9");
 Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
 System.out.print("Enter your name: ");
 String name = scanner.nextLine();
 System.out.print("Enter your roll number: ");
 String rollNo = scanner.nextLine();
 System.out.print("Enter your percentage: ");
 String percentage = scanner.nextLine();
 System.out.println("Name: " + name);
 System.out.println("Roll No: " + rollNo);
 System.out.println("Percentage: " + percentage);
 }
}




Write a program to accept year from the user and check whether it is leap year or not.

import java.util.*;
public class LeapYear {
 public static void main(String[] args) {
 System.out.println("Irfan Ali, Rollno: 9");
 Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
 System.out.print("Enter a year: ");
 int year = scanner.nextInt();
 if ((year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0) || (year % 400 == 0)) {
 System.out.println(year + " is a leap year.");
 } else {
 System.out.println(year + " is not a leap year.");
 }
 }
}
